The second likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the data set is based on AI planning problems. The third likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the paper mentions labeling the graphs. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper discusses the challenges of computing graph models.
